# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

Add a new fictitious **PulseBoard** channel to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post to named *boards* (group) and send direct messages (DM). It must support both chat types, authenticate via API key, and cap text chunks at 4,000 characters. The implementation follows the exact same extension structure as the bundled IRC plugin (the closest structural match: both channels support group + direct, both use API-key auth patterns, neither requires a heavy third-party SDK).

**Constraint:** Only new files may be created, all inside `extensions/pulseboard/`. No existing files are touched.

---

## Directory Layout

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── package.json                  # npm metadata + openclaw channel block
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # minimal plugin manifest
├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry entry point
├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry for wizard
├── api.ts                        # public barrel (accounts + setup-surface)
├── channel-config-api.ts         # exports PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                  # domain types
    ├── accounts.ts               # ResolvedPulseBoardAccount + helpers
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schemas + buildChannelConfigSchema
    ├── config-ui-hints.ts        # UI hints for config fields
    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── runtime-api.ts            # private barrel → openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc
    ├── channel.ts                # createChatChannelPlugin (main plugin object)
    ├── client.ts                 # PulseBoardClient (fictional HTTP/WS transport)
    ├── normalize.ts              # target + allowlist normalizers
    ├── policy.ts                 # group-match + mention-gate helpers
    ├── inbound.ts                # handlePulseBoardInbound
    ├── send.ts                   # sendMessagePulseBoard
    ├── monitor.ts                # monitorPulseBoardProvider (gateway loop)
    ├── probe.ts                  # probePulseBoard (status health check)
    ├── setup-core.ts             # config mutation helpers + ChannelSetupAdapter
    ├── setup-surface.ts          # ChannelSetupWizard (interactive prompts)
    ├── channel.test.ts           # outbound chunker smoke test
    └── normalize.test.ts         # target + allowlist normalizer tests
```

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest. Pattern is identical across all channel plugins.

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

### Step 2 — `package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "install": { "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1" },
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (API Key)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "real-time bulletin board platform with board channels and direct messages.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board"],
      "systemImage": "chart.bar.doc.horizontal"
    }
  }
}
```

No `dependencies` block — the fictional transport is implemented with native `fetch`/`setInterval`; no third-party libs needed.

### Step 3 — `src/types.ts`

Core domain types:

```typescript
export type PulseBoardBoardConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  tools?: GroupToolPolicyConfig;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  apiKey?: string;
  apiKeyFile?: string;
  botUserId?: string;
  serverUrl?: string;
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  boards?: Record<string, PulseBoardBoardConfig>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  blockStreaming?: boolean;
};

export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  boardId?: string;        // board name when isGroup=true
  senderId: string;        // sender user ID
  senderName?: string;     // display name (optional)
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

export type PulseBoardProbe = BaseProbeResult<string> & {
  serverUrl: string;
  botUserId: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
};
```

Types import `DmPolicy`, `GroupPolicy`, `GroupToolPolicyConfig`, `BaseProbeResult`, `OpenClawConfig` from `./runtime-api.js`.

