# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

Add a new fictitious **PulseBoard** channel to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post to named *boards* (group) and send direct messages (DM). It must support both chat types, authenticate via API key, and cap text chunks at 4,000 characters. The implementation follows the exact same extension structure as the bundled IRC plugin (the closest structural match: both channels support group + direct, both use API-key auth patterns, neither requires a heavy third-party SDK).

**Constraint:** Only new files may be created, all inside `extensions/pulseboard/`. No existing files are touched.

---

## Directory Layout

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── package.json                  # npm metadata + openclaw channel block
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # minimal plugin manifest
├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry entry point
├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry for wizard
├── api.ts                        # public barrel (accounts + setup-surface)
├── channel-config-api.ts         # exports PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                  # domain types
    ├── accounts.ts               # ResolvedPulseBoardAccount + helpers
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schemas + buildChannelConfigSchema
    ├── config-ui-hints.ts        # UI hints for config fields
    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── runtime-api.ts            # private barrel → openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc
    ├── channel.ts                # createChatChannelPlugin (main plugin object)
    ├── client.ts                 # PulseBoardClient (fictional HTTP/WS transport)
    ├── normalize.ts              # target + allowlist normalizers
    ├── policy.ts                 # group-match + mention-gate helpers
    ├── inbound.ts                # handlePulseBoardInbound
    ├── send.ts                   # sendMessagePulseBoard
    ├── monitor.ts                # monitorPulseBoardProvider (gateway loop)
    ├── probe.ts                  # probePulseBoard (status health check)
    ├── setup-core.ts             # config mutation helpers + ChannelSetupAdapter
    ├── setup-surface.ts          # ChannelSetupWizard (interactive prompts)
    ├── channel.test.ts           # outbound chunker smoke test
    └── normalize.test.ts         # target + allowlist normalizer tests
```

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest. Pattern is identical across all channel plugins.

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

### Step 2 — `package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "install": { "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1" },
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (API Key)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "real-time bulletin board platform with board channels and direct messages.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board"],
      "systemImage": "chart.bar.doc.horizontal"
    }
  }
}
```

No `dependencies` block — the fictional transport is implemented with native `fetch`/`setInterval`; no third-party libs needed.

### Step 3 — `src/types.ts`

Core domain types:

```typescript
export type PulseBoardBoardConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  tools?: GroupToolPolicyConfig;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  apiKey?: string;
  apiKeyFile?: string;
  botUserId?: string;
  serverUrl?: string;
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  boards?: Record<string, PulseBoardBoardConfig>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  blockStreaming?: boolean;
};

export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  boardId?: string;        // board name when isGroup=true
  senderId: string;        // sender user ID
  senderName?: string;     // display name (optional)
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

export type PulseBoardProbe = BaseProbeResult<string> & {
  serverUrl: string;
  botUserId: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
};
```

Types import `DmPolicy`, `GroupPolicy`, `GroupToolPolicyConfig`, `BaseProbeResult`, `OpenClawConfig` from `./runtime-api.js`.

### Step 4 — `src/runtime-api.ts`

Private barrel. Imports all generic channel-runtime helpers from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` (listed as a public entrypoint in `scripts/lib/plugin-sdk-entrypoints.json`). This is the same surface the IRC plugin uses; no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` subpath exists and cannot be created under the file-creation constraint.

```typescript
// Private runtime barrel for the bundled PulseBoard extension.
export {
  buildBaseChannelStatusSummary,
  createAccountStatusSink,
  chunkTextForOutbound,
  createChannelPairingController,
  DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID,
  deliverFormattedTextWithAttachments,
  dispatchInboundReplyWithBase,
  getChatChannelMeta,
  GROUP_POLICY_BLOCKED_LABEL,
  isDangerousNameMatchingEnabled,
  logInboundDrop,
  PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE,
  readStoreAllowFromForDmPolicy,
  resolveAllowlistProviderRuntimeGroupPolicy,
  resolveControlCommandGate,
  resolveDefaultGroupPolicy,
  resolveEffectiveAllowFromLists,
  warnMissingProviderGroupPolicyFallbackOnce,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc";
export type {
  BaseProbeResult,
  BlockStreamingCoalesceConfig,
  ChannelPlugin,
  DmConfig,
  DmPolicy,
  GroupPolicy,
  GroupToolPolicyBySenderConfig,
  GroupToolPolicyConfig,
  MarkdownConfig,
  OpenClawConfig,
  OutboundReplyPayload,
  PluginRuntime,
  RuntimeEnv,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc";
```

### Step 5 — `src/runtime.ts`

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "./runtime-api.js";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");
export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };
export function clearPulseBoardRuntime() {
  setPulseBoardRuntime(undefined as unknown as PluginRuntime);
}
```

### Step 6 — `src/accounts.ts`

Exports `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`, `listPulseBoardAccountIds`, `resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId`, `resolvePulseBoardAccount`, `listEnabledPulseBoardAccounts`.

Resolution priority for `apiKey`:
1. `PULSEBOARD_API_KEY` env var (default account only)
2. `apiKeyFile` path (via `tryReadSecretFileSync`)
3. `config.apiKey` (via `normalizeResolvedSecretInputString`)

Resolution priority for `botUserId`:
1. `PULSEBOARD_BOT_USER_ID` env var (default account only)
2. `config.botUserId`

Resolution for `serverUrl`:
1. `PULSEBOARD_SERVER_URL` env var (default account only)
2. `config.serverUrl`
3. Default: `"https://pulseboard.example.com"`

`configured` is `true` when both `apiKey` and `botUserId` are non-empty.

SDK imports used:
- `createAccountListHelpers` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers`
- `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`, `normalizeAccountId` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id`
- `resolveMergedAccountConfig` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution`
- `tryReadSecretFileSync` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`
- `normalizeResolvedSecretInputString` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input`

### Step 7 — `src/config-schema.ts`

Zod schema following the IRC pattern exactly. Key fields:

```typescript
const PulseBoardBoardSchema = z.object({
  requireMention: z.boolean().optional(),
  tools: ToolPolicySchema,
  enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
  allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
  systemPrompt: z.string().optional(),
}).strict();

const PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase = z.object({
  name: z.string().optional(),
  enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
  apiKey: z.string().optional(),
  apiKeyFile: z.string().optional(),
  botUserId: z.string().optional(),
  serverUrl: z.string().url().optional(),
  dmPolicy: DmPolicySchema.optional().default("pairing"),
  allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
  groupPolicy: GroupPolicySchema.optional().default("allowlist"),
  groupAllowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
  boards: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardBoardSchema.optional()).optional(),
  defaultTo: z.string().optional(),
  ...ReplyRuntimeConfigSchemaShape,
}).strict();

export const PulseBoardConfigSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.extend({
  accounts: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardAccountSchema.optional()).optional(),
  defaultAccount: z.string().optional(),
}).superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({ policy: value.dmPolicy, allowFrom: value.allowFrom, ctx, ... });
});

export const PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema = buildChannelConfigSchema(
  PulseBoardConfigSchema,
  { uiHints: pulseBoardChannelConfigUiHints },
);
```

SDK imports: `buildChannelConfigSchema`, `DmPolicySchema`, `GroupPolicySchema`, `ToolPolicySchema`, `ReplyRuntimeConfigSchemaShape`, `requireOpenAllowFrom` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema`; `z` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod`.

### Step 8 — `src/config-ui-hints.ts`

`ChannelConfigUiHint` records for `""` (root), `apiKey`, `botUserId`, `serverUrl`, `dmPolicy`. Follows the same `satisfies Record<string, ChannelConfigUiHint>` pattern as `irc/src/config-ui-hints.ts`.

### Step 9 — `src/normalize.ts`

```
isBoardTarget(target)          → starts with "#" or "board:"
normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(raw) → strips "pulseboard:", "board:", "user:" prefixes,
                                          returns undefined for invalid targets
looksLikePulseBoardTargetId(raw)        → /^[^\s:]+$/u (no spaces or colons)
normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(raw)      → strips "pulseboard:", "user:" prefixes; lowercase
normalizePulseBoardAllowlist(entries)   → maps entries through normalizeEntry, filters empty
resolvePulseBoardAllowlistMatch(...)    → exact set match (same as IRC allowlist match)
formatPulseBoardSenderId(message)       → "senderId" or "senderId(senderName)"
buildPulseBoardAllowlistCandidates(message) → [senderId, "senderId(senderName)"] candidates
```

### Step 10 — `src/policy.ts`

Mirrors `irc/src/policy.ts` exactly with PulseBoard type names:
- `resolvePulseBoardGroupMatch({ boards, target })` → `PulseBoardGroupMatch`
- `resolvePulseBoardGroupAccessGate({ groupPolicy, groupMatch })` → `PulseBoardGroupAccessGate`
- `resolvePulseBoardRequireMention({ boardConfig, wildcardConfig })` → `boolean`
- `resolvePulseBoardMentionGate(...)` → `{ shouldSkip, reason }`
- `resolvePulseBoardGroupSenderAllowed(...)` → `boolean`

### Step 11 — `src/client.ts`

Fictional PulseBoard transport layer (no real network calls, but structured as if real):

```typescript
export type PulseBoardClientOptions = {
  serverUrl: string;
  apiKey: string;
  botUserId: string;
  boards?: string[];          // boards to subscribe to
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
  onMessage?: (event: PulseBoardEvent) => Promise<void>;
  onError?: (err: Error) => void;
};

export type PulseBoardEvent = {
  type: "board_message" | "direct_message";
  messageId: string;
  boardId?: string;           // present for board_message
  senderId: string;
  senderName?: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
};

export type PulseBoardClient = {
  sendBoardMessage(boardId: string, text: string): void;
  sendDirectMessage(userId: string, text: string): void;
  disconnect(): void;
};

export async function connectPulseBoardClient(
  opts: PulseBoardClientOptions,
): Promise<PulseBoardClient>;
```

Internally uses `setInterval` polling + `fetch` (via the PulseBoard fictional REST API) to simulate a persistent connection. The polling loop fires `opts.onMessage` for each event. The client respects `opts.abortSignal` to stop polling cleanly.

### Step 12 — `src/probe.ts`

```typescript
export async function probePulseBoard(
  cfg: CoreConfig,
  opts?: { accountId?: string; timeoutMs?: number },
): Promise<PulseBoardProbe>
```

Makes a `GET /api/health` request to `account.serverUrl` with the API key in the `Authorization: Bearer <apiKey>` header. Returns `ok: true` with `latencyMs` on success, or `ok: false` with `error` message on failure. Uses `AbortSignal.timeout(opts?.timeoutMs ?? 8000)`.

### Step 13 — `src/send.ts`

```typescript
export async function sendMessagePulseBoard(
  to: string,
  text: string,
  opts: SendPulseBoardOptions = {},
): Promise<SendPulseBoardResult>
```

- Resolves account from config
- Normalizes target (`to`) via `normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget`
- Detects `isBoardTarget` to route to `POST /api/boards/{boardId}/messages` or `POST /api/dms/{userId}/messages`
- Passes `Authorization: Bearer <apiKey>` header
- Records outbound activity via `getPulseBoardRuntime().channel.activity.record(...)`

### Step 14 — `src/inbound.ts`

`handlePulseBoardInbound({ message, account, config, runtime, sendReply, statusSink })` mirrors `irc/src/inbound.ts` closely:

1. Trim raw body; return early if empty
2. Record `lastInboundAt` on statusSink
3. Resolve `dmPolicy`, `groupPolicy` via `resolveAllowlistProviderRuntimeGroupPolicy`
4. For group messages: resolve board match via `resolvePulseBoardGroupMatch`, check `resolvePulseBoardGroupAccessGate`, check sender allowed via `resolvePulseBoardGroupSenderAllowed`
5. For DMs: enforce `dmPolicy` (disabled / pairing / allowlist check) via `readStoreAllowFromForDmPolicy` + `resolveEffectiveAllowFromLists`
6. Check mention gate via `resolvePulseBoardMentionGate`
7. Build `ctxPayload` via `core.channel.reply.finalizeInboundContext`
8. Dispatch via `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase`
9. Deliver reply chunks via `deliverFormattedTextWithAttachments` + `sendMessagePulseBoard`

### Step 15 — `src/monitor.ts`

```typescript
export async function monitorPulseBoardProvider(
  opts: PulseBoardMonitorOptions,
): Promise<{ stop: () => void }>
```

1. Resolves account via `resolvePulseBoardAccount`
2. Calls `connectPulseBoardClient` with `onMessage` callback
3. `onMessage` wraps each `PulseBoardEvent` into a `PulseBoardInboundMessage` and calls `handlePulseBoardInbound`
4. Returns `{ stop: () => client.disconnect() }`

### Step 16 — `src/channel.ts`

Main plugin definition. Uses `createChatChannelPlugin` with:

```typescript
capabilities: {
  chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
  media: false,              // PulseBoard: text-only boards
  blockStreaming: true,
},
reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },

// outbound
outbound: {
  base: {
    deliveryMode: "direct",
    chunker: chunkTextForOutbound,
    chunkerMode: "markdown",
    textChunkLimit: 4000,    // PulseBoard platform limit
  },
  attachedResults: { channel: "pulseboard", sendText, sendMedia },
},
```

Also includes: `config` adapter via `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`, `groups`, `messaging`, `resolver`, `directory` via `createChannelDirectoryAdapter`, `status` via `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter`, `gateway.startAccount` via `runStoppablePassiveMonitor` + `monitorPulseBoardProvider`, `pairing.text` with `idLabel: "pulseBoardUser"`, `security` with DM policy resolver + warning collector.

### Step 17 — `src/setup-core.ts`

Config mutation helpers mirroring `irc/src/setup-core.ts`:
- `updatePulseBoardAccountConfig(cfg, accountId, patch)` via `patchScopedAccountConfig`
- `setPulseBoardDmPolicy(cfg, dmPolicy)` via `createTopLevelChannelDmPolicySetter`
- `setPulseBoardAllowFrom(cfg, allowFrom)` via `createTopLevelChannelAllowFromSetter`
- `setPulseBoardGroupAccess(cfg, accountId, policy, entries, normalizeEntry)`
- `pulseBoardSetupAdapter: ChannelSetupAdapter` — `resolveAccountId`, `applyAccountName`, `validateInput` (requires `apiKey` + `botUserId`), `applyAccountConfig`

### Step 18 — `src/setup-surface.ts`

`pulseBoardSetupWizard: ChannelSetupWizard` with:
- `status`: `createStandardChannelSetupStatus` (configured = apiKey + botUserId present)
- `introNote`: description of PulseBoard config; env var list: `PULSEBOARD_API_KEY`, `PULSEBOARD_BOT_USER_ID`, `PULSEBOARD_SERVER_URL`
- `prepare`: check env vars; offer to use them
- `textInputs`: prompts for server URL, bot user ID, API key, default board subscriptions
- `groupAccess`: board allowlist (normalizes `board:<name>` or `#board-name` entries)
- `allowFrom`: user allowlist for DMs
- `dmPolicy`: `ircDmPolicy`-style block reusing `createTopLevelChannelDmPolicy`
- `finalize`: prompt `requireMention` for boards; optional server URL confirmation
- `completionNote`: restart + verify instructions
- `disable`: `setSetupChannelEnabled(cfg, channel, false)`

### Step 19 — Root entry files

**`index.ts`:**
```typescript
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
